cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with the problem of testing and generating greedy rectilinear drawings of planar graphs, which involves topics such as computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and network routing (cs.NI). The use of rectilinear edges and the focus on human readability also suggest a possible connection to visualization (cs.HC). However, since the paper does not explicitly discuss user studies or interface design, we do not include cs.HC in the list of likely sub-categories.
